    "text": "58% is rough this time of year. Are you running a cool-mist humidifier under the bench or just the fogger? My Phals sulk below 60.",
    "timestamp": "2026-10-12T07:00:46+00:00",
    "user_id": "17841400000000002",
    "username": "midohio_grower"
  },
  {
    "hidden": "false",
    "id": "18000000000000001",
    "like_count": 6,
    "media_id": "17900000000000001",
    "parent_id": null,
    "text": "Roots like that on a roth after winter is genuinely impressive. What bark grade are you using — fine or medium?",
    "timestamp": "2026-10-12T20:52:38+00:00",
    "user_id": "17841400000000003",
    "username": "paph_keeper_614"
  },
  {
    "hidden": "false",
    "id": "18000000000000002",
    "like_count": 22,
    "media_id": "17900000000000002",
    "parent_id": null,
    "text": "Three years of patience and there it is. That's a benching-quality Cattleya — the Midwest Regional judges are going to love it.",
    "timestamp": "2026-10-12T20:31:32+00:00",
    "user_id": "17841400000000004",
    "username": "windsweptorchids"
  },
  {
    "hidden": "false",
    "id": "18000000000000003",
    "like_count": 25,
    "media_id": "17900000000000003",
    "parent_id": null,
    "text": "Soda bread AND a blooming Cattleya in the same week. The rest of us are not okay. Recipe in the highlights still?",
    "timestamp": "2026-10-09T06:50:23+00:00",
    "user_id": "17841400000000005",
    "username": "dailysodabread"
  },
  {
    "hidden": "false",
    "id": "18000000000000004",
    "like_count": 4,
    "media_id": "17900000000000000",
    "parent_id": null,
    "text": "Same fight here every October. I cracked and put a second fogger on a timer — best thing I did all season for the spiking Phals.",
    "timestamp": "2026-10-09T21:35:38+00:00",
    "user_id": "17841400000000006",
    "username": "fpconservatory"
  },
  {
    "hidden": "false",
    "id": "18000000000000005",
    "like_count": 9,
    "media_id": "17900000000000002",
    "parent_id": null,
    "text": "Lovely form on that Cattleya. I'm bringing my Paph again this year so consider the gauntlet thrown for December, Jean.",
    "timestamp": "2026-10-08T00:45:02+00:00",
    "user_id": "17841400000000007",
    "username": "dorothy_kendall_orchids"
  },
  {
    "hidden": "false",
    "id": "18000000000000006",
    "like_count": 5,
    "media_id": "17900000000000001",
    "parent_id": null,
    "text": "That bark and perlite blend has been my go-to for slipper orchids too. Glad the roots came through the winter clean.",
    "timestamp": "2026-10-12T11:14:09+00:00",
    "user_id": "17841400000000008",
    "username": "rooted_in_ohio"
  },
  {
    "hidden": "false",
    "id": "18000000000000007",
    "like_count": 11,
    "media_id": "17900000000000002",
    "parent_id": null,
    "text": "Benching-quality is right. The color saturation on that lip is gorgeous — good luck at the Midwest Regional in December.",
    "timestamp": "2026-10-12T21:40:17+00:00",
    "user_id": "17841400000000009",
    "username": "cattleya_corner"
  },
  {
    "hidden": "false",
    "id": "18000000000000008",
    "like_count": 3,
    "media_id": "17900000000000000",
    "parent_id": null,
    "text": "Same dawn-fogger routine here in Worthington. Once the spikes set I stop fussing — they toughen up by November.",
    "timestamp": "2026-10-11T08:02:55+00:00",
    "user_id": "17841400000000010",
    "username": "worthington_blooms"
  },
  {
    "hidden": "false",
    "id": "18000000000000009",
    "like_count": 7,
    "media_id": "17900000000000003",
    "parent_id": null,
    "text": "Cold butter and a light hand, exactly. My gran would approve. Saving this before the next Society meeting bake sale.",
    "timestamp": "2026-10-11T14:48:31+00:00",
    "user_id": "17841400000000011",
    "username": "irish_kitchen_jan"
  },
  {
    "hidden": "false",
    "id": "18000000000000010",
    "like_count": 2,
    "media_id": "17900000000000001",
    "parent_id": null,
    "text": "Rothschildianum is such a patient plant. Did you bump up the pot size or keep it snug this round?",
    "timestamp": "2026-10-12T16:25:44+00:00",
    "user_id": "17841400000000012",
    "username": "slipperseeker"
  },
  {
    "hidden": "false",
    "id": "18000000000000011",
    "like_count": 14,
    "media_id": "17900000000000002",
    "parent_id": null,
    "text": "Three winters of Columbus and it rewards you like this. Putting it on the show table is the easy part now.",
    "timestamp": "2026-10-12T22:05:12+00:00",
    "user_id": "17841400000000013",
    "username": "midwestregional_aos"
  },
  {
    "hidden": "false",
    "id": "18000000000000012",
    "like_count": 1,
    "media_id": "17900000000000000",
    "parent_id": null,
    "text": "58% would have my Masdevallias melting. Respect to anyone overwintering Phals in a basement greenhouse.",
    "timestamp": "2026-10-11T09:37:20+00:00",
    "user_id": "17841400000000014",
    "username": "coolgrower_oh"
  },
  {
    "hidden": "false",
    "id": "18000000000000013",
    "like_count": 9,
    "media_id": "17900000000000003",
    "parent_id": null,
    "text": "Brown soda bread is criminally underrated. Add a handful of oats next time — keeps it tender for days.",
    "timestamp": "2026-10-12T07:51:03+00:00",
    "user_id": "17841400000000015",
    "username": "the_dublin_baker"
  },
  {
    "hidden": "false",
    "id": "18000000000000014",
    "like_count": 4,
    "media_id": "17900000000000002",
    "parent_id": null,
    "text": "Staging six for the regional is ambitious and I love it. Will you bring the Paph too or just the Cattleyas?",
    "timestamp": "2026-10-12T18:09:48+00:00",
    "user_id": "17841400000000016",
    "username": "showbench_notes"
  },
  {
    "hidden": "false",
    "id": "18000000000000015",
    "like_count": 6,
    "media_id": "17900000000000001",
    "parent_id": null,
    "text": "No rot after a Midwest winter is a genuine win. Your aftercare videos got me through my first repot — thank you.",
    "timestamp": "2026-10-12T13:22:37+00:00",
    "user_id": "17841400000000017",
    "username": "newgrower_emma_m"
  },
  {
    "hidden": "false",
    "id": "18000000000000016",
    "like_count": 3,
    "media_id": "17900000000000000",
    "parent_id": null,
    "text": "Running two small foggers on a humidistat changed everything for my spiking Phals. Worth every penny.",
    "timestamp": "2026-10-11T19:44:15+00:00",
    "user_id": "17841400000000018",
    "username": "buckeye_orchids"
  },
  {
    "hidden": "false",
    "id": "18000000000000017",
    "like_count": 8,
    "media_id": "17900000000000003",
    "parent_id": null,
    "text": "Twenty minutes for soda bread, then back to the bench — the correct order of operations. Beautiful crumb, Jean.",
